      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="1">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">B</span>
        <span class="opt-text">client-based</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="2">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">C</span>
        <span class="opt-text">peer-to-peer (P2P)</span>
      </button>
      <button class="option-btn" data-idx="3">
        <span class="opt-indicator"></span>
        <span class="opt-letter">D</span>
        <span class="opt-text">master-slave</span>
      </button>
    </div>

    <div class="submit-wrap" style="display: none;">
      <button class="submit-btn" id="submit-46" disabled>Submit Answer</button>
    </div>

    <div class="explanation" id="exp-46">
      <div class="exp-header">
        <span class="exp-verdict" id="verdict-46"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="exp-body">
        Peer-to-peer (P2P) networks have two or more network devices that can share resources such as printers or files without having a dedicated server.
      </div>
